text: thumb Florian Billant (born July 7, 1996, Gravelines) is a French handball player, was in favor of the French HC Dunkerque.Dunkerque: Billant signe son premier contrat In 2015, in Brazil as part of the national team of France U21 won the world title. In 2016 he participated in the European Championship among youth (U20), where the French team won a bronze medal, played 7 games and scored 21 goal. ==References== ==External links== * Passport Florian Billant * Florian Billant Player Info * Interview Category:1996 births Category:French male handball players Category:Living people
